00:24:18.064 --> 00:24:21.644
been recently described over the last couple of years in these

407
00:24:21.684 --> 00:24:25.484
patients. We used to think it was sort of rare, and now we're doing more and

408
00:24:25.664 --> 00:24:29.584
we're seeing more. And so for the younger patients who tend to

409
00:24:29.624 --> 00:24:33.444
have the phenotypes, you can still do a clinical diagnosis without telomere

