set up this conversation. So I am a head

983
00:58:30.226 --> 00:58:33.766
neck surgeon, and when I was training, head neck cancer

984
00:58:33.776 --> 00:58:37.446
happened in people who had long histories of

985
00:58:37.486 --> 00:58:41.196
tobacco exposure, usually smoking cigarettes, usually in

986
00:58:41.246 --> 00:58:44.706
combination with use of alcohol. In my

987
00:58:44.766 --> 00:58:48.696
lifetime, we've seen an emergence of a whole new category of head neck

988
00:58:48.766 --> 00:58:52.646
cancer, which is HPV positive head neck cancer.

989
00:58:53.106 --> 00:58:54.306
But because

990
00:58:55.406 --> 00:58:57.786
children with Fanconi anemia

991
00:58:58.906 --> 00:59:02.406
died largely before they became adults,

992
00:59:03.146 --> 00:59:05.626
we never heard about Fanconi anemia.

993
00:59:05.746 --> 00:59:09.226
We never saw a patient with head neck cancer who had

994
00:59:09.286 --> 00:59:12.846
Fanconi anemia. And I remember I was with Alan D'Andrea

995
00:59:13.226 --> 00:59:17.166
at a meeting, and we were suddenly aware that

996
00:59:17.206 --> 00:59:20.906
people with Fanconi anemia were developing head neck

997
00:59:20.926 --> 00:59:24.576
cancer, and we thought, "Oh, it's HPV." But it's

998
00:59:24.786 --> 00:59:28.666
not HPV. So now I'm going to tell you a little bit about

999
00:59:28.786 --> 00:59:32.566
my journey, both as a clinician and as an investigator, trying to

1000
00:59:32.646 --> 00:59:36.466
understand this problem that is extraordinarily urgent.

1001
00:59:36.906 --> 00:59:40.826
I am part of the Fanconi Cancer Foundation, formerly Fanconi Anemia

1002
00:59:40.886 --> 00:59:44.646
Research Foundation, and we coordinate a virtual

1003
00:59:44.706 --> 00:59:47.946
tumor board for families and clinicians.

1004
00:59:47.956 --> 00:59:51.866
Most clinicians are seeing their first and probably only patient

1005
00:59:51.906 --> 00:59:54.796
with head neck cancer who has Fanconi anemia.

1006
00:59:54.876 --> 00:59:58.796
They don't know what to do. And, I think it's not

1007
00:59:58.826 --> 01:00:02.296
unfair to say that we have at least one tumor board a week

1008
01:00:02.806 --> 01:00:04.726
serving clinicians all over the world.

1009
01:00:04.786 --> 01:00:06.226
This is an extraordinarily

1010
01:00:07.426 --> 01:00:11.146
increasing and urgent problem. So, as I mentioned,

1011
01:00:11.866 --> 01:00:12.766
these children

1012
01:00:14.306 --> 01:00:17.176
typically presented early in life. Dr.

1013
01:00:17.386 --> 01:00:21.286
Savage described many of the different phenotypes that they

1014
01:00:21.326 --> 01:00:22.326
would present with,

1015
01:00:23.406 --> 01:00:27.266
characterized by germline defects in DNA repair genes

1016
01:00:27.286 --> 01:00:31.146
that have been very well-characterized over the last 20 to 30

1017
01:00:31.306 --> 01:00:35.186
years. And sometimes we will see an adult

1018
01:00:35.246 --> 01:00:38.126
patient, no diagnosis of Fanconi anemia.

1019
01:00:38.506 --> 01:00:42.326
They have head neck cancer. They're given platinum

1020
01:00:42.426 --> 01:00:46.186
or radiation without an awareness of the need for dose reduction.

1021
01:00:46.206 --> 01:00:50.166
They'll have an extraordinary toxic reaction, and then they will go through

1022
01:00:50.206 --> 01:00:54.006
the diagnostic process and turn out to have a form of

1023
01:00:54.016 --> 01:00:55.226
Fanconi anemia.

1024
01:00:56.046 --> 01:00:59.896
So what you saw in Dr. Savage's talk is

1025
01:01:00.006 --> 01:01:03.886
all the data. The good news is that bone marrow

1026
01:01:03.926 --> 01:01:07.586
transplant or hematopoietic stem cell transplant has

1027
01:01:07.646 --> 01:01:11.576
saved the lives of these children, and they're now living into

1028
01:01:11.606 --> 01:01:13.326
their teenage years and adulthood.

1029
01:01:13.726 --> 01:01:16.366
The consequence, though, is they have an

1030
01:01:16.406 --> 01:01:20.146
extraordinarily high risk for developing solid

1031
01:01:20.186 --> 01:01:22.662
tumors. And I'm going to say this...

1032
01:01:22.672 --> 01:01:24.382
clearly because it's still

1033
01:01:25.782 --> 01:01:29.122
not understood at all. Why would

1034
01:01:29.182 --> 01:01:32.942
these people get squamous cell carcinoma of the oral

1035
01:01:32.962 --> 01:01:35.482
cavity? We do not understand this.

1036
01:01:35.582 --> 01:01:39.522
We have lumped head neck cancer as one etiology over

1037
01:01:39.562 --> 01:01:43.102
the years. Maybe now it's HPV positive versus HPV

1038
01:01:43.242 --> 01:01:47.082
negative, but what is it about the mucosa of

1039
01:01:47.122 --> 01:01:50.462
the oral cavity that puts these individuals at such an

1040
01:01:50.482 --> 01:01:54.362
extraordinarily high risk? It's 500, 600, 700

1041
01:01:54.372 --> 01:01:58.132
fold increased incidence. We don't understand it, but it says something that is

1042
01:01:58.162 --> 01:02:02.102
something fundamentally important about DNA repair

1043
01:02:02.122 --> 01:02:05.802
in oral carcinogenesis, and we simply don't understand this very

1044
01:02:05.902 --> 01:02:09.502
well. So in addition, the vast majority of the

1045
01:02:09.542 --> 01:02:13.442
patients in our virtual tumor board have head neck cancer, but

1046
01:02:13.502 --> 01:02:17.402
increasingly we are seeing individuals with esophageal cancer,

1047
01:02:18.042 --> 01:02:21.982
vulvar cancer. Last week it was liver cancer, the week before it was breast

1048
01:02:22.022 --> 01:02:25.922
cancer. So it's more commonly head neck cancer, but it's certainly

1049
01:02:25.982 --> 01:02:27.961
not isolated to head neck cancer.

1050
01:02:28.822 --> 01:02:32.082
And as emphasized by Dr. Savage, our treatment

1051
01:02:32.242 --> 01:02:35.662
options are profoundly limited,

1052
01:02:36.122 --> 01:02:39.542
and there are a couple of understandable limitations.

1053
01:02:40.042 --> 01:02:43.662
Even though I am bombarded with these individuals in

1054
01:02:43.682 --> 01:02:46.982
my academic now practice, it's a very small patient

1055
01:02:47.062 --> 01:02:50.982
population. It's maybe 1,000 people right now

1056
01:02:51.062 --> 01:02:54.922
in the United States living with Fanconi anemia.

1057
01:02:55.522 --> 01:02:59.082
And so clinical trials historically have

1058
01:02:59.122 --> 01:03:02.562
excluded any individual with this kind of

1059
01:03:02.802 --> 01:03:04.602
inherited predisposition syndrome.

1060
01:03:05.162 --> 01:03:08.962
And to my knowledge, the only trial that

1061
01:03:09.022 --> 01:03:12.962
has ever been implemented for head neck cancer in Fanconi anemia

1062
01:03:13.002 --> 01:03:16.372
patients is happening in Europe, spearheaded by

1063
01:03:16.742 --> 01:03:20.042
investigators in Spain, and it's looking at an oral

1064
01:03:20.462 --> 01:03:24.422
EGFR tyrosine kinase inhibitor. And we'll talk a little bit about the

1065
01:03:24.502 --> 01:03:28.342
opportunities and some of the challenge with picking one agent

1066
01:03:28.402 --> 01:03:31.911
for what I'm going to show you is an incredibly heterogeneous population.

1067
01:03:32.942 --> 01:03:36.642
We've learned the hard way that they cannot get

1068
01:03:36.902 --> 01:03:38.791
systemic chemotherapy, that

1069
01:03:40.002 --> 01:03:43.562
is way too toxic. There are ways to deliver radiation.

1070
01:03:43.602 --> 01:03:47.442
We've had some very dedicated radiation oncologists who have worked out a

1071
01:03:47.482 --> 01:03:50.601
dose reduction schema or a dose testing schema.

1072
01:03:50.722 --> 01:03:53.202
Many of these patients are trying protons

1073
01:03:54.102 --> 01:03:57.851
to a largely beneficial effect. We've reviewed all the cases in the

1074
01:03:57.922 --> 01:04:01.482
literature, and it is safe to give radiation, but one must be

1075
01:04:01.542 --> 01:04:05.482
aware of the toxicity and proceed appropriately.

1076
01:04:06.382 --> 01:04:10.222
And the animal models simply don't

1077
01:04:10.282 --> 01:04:13.942
exist. They're very limited. They aren't readily

1078
01:04:13.982 --> 01:04:17.972
extrapolatable to most clinical settings, and we don't have any clinical

1079
01:04:18.042 --> 01:04:21.702
trial data. So I'm going to tell you about what we

1080
01:04:21.722 --> 01:04:25.562
decided to do. So I am here with my research

1081
01:04:25.622 --> 01:04:28.992
partner, Dan Johnson, who's in the audience, and Agata

1082
01:04:29.022 --> 01:04:32.682
Smogorzewska, who is an investigator, a pathologist, a

1083
01:04:32.722 --> 01:04:36.702
scientist from Rockefeller. Rockefeller had housed one of

1084
01:04:36.742 --> 01:04:40.552
the original databases, family collections of

1085
01:04:40.642 --> 01:04:44.302
patients with Fanconi anemia. And what Agata did with a team of

1086
01:04:44.362 --> 01:04:48.082
international collaborators, it probably took 20 years to

1087
01:04:48.122 --> 01:04:52.082
accumulate these specimens. So I had the privilege and honor of being one of

1088
01:04:52.122 --> 01:04:55.062
the leaders of the head neck cancer TCGA effort.

1089
01:04:55.562 --> 01:04:59.472
So when Agata was trying to accumulate samples and

1090
01:04:59.502 --> 01:05:03.482
do essentially a TCGA on head neck cancer

1091
01:05:03.542 --> 01:05:07.322
in Fanconi patients, we had a lot of deep

1092
01:05:07.802 --> 01:05:11.252
conversations, and the first expectation was that

1093
01:05:11.342 --> 01:05:13.522
these cancers would be different.

1094
01:05:14.022 --> 01:05:16.382
And I'm going to cut to the chase, they're not.

1095
01:05:17.662 --> 01:05:18.462
Other than the

1096
01:05:19.322 --> 01:05:23.102
penetration of the germline defects in DNA repair, most of these

1097
01:05:23.482 --> 01:05:25.622
individuals have defects in FANC A.

1098
01:05:26.642 --> 01:05:29.502
The compendium of genetic

1099
01:05:29.562 --> 01:05:33.142
alterations in the head neck cancers from Fanconi patients

1100
01:05:33.562 --> 01:05:37.042
are exactly like the head neck cancers from patients with

1101
01:05:37.082 --> 01:05:40.742
sporadic head neck cancer. So no smoking gun, no obvious

1102
01:05:40.842 --> 01:05:44.362
target. So what we have done in our lab for decades

1103
01:05:44.702 --> 01:05:48.662
is we figured out a long time ago that our cell lines were

1104
01:05:48.742 --> 01:05:52.682
so distantly related to the patients that we were treating that we needed to

1105
01:05:52.702 --> 01:05:56.182
develop new models. So we've developed over the years probably close to

1106
01:05:56.262 --> 01:05:59.512
100 patient-derived xenografts from sporadic head neck

1107
01:05:59.562 --> 01:06:03.142
cancers. There were no such models for Fanconi anemia

1108
01:06:03.222 --> 01:06:07.182
patients, so we decided with support from the Fanconi Cancer Foundation

1109
01:06:07.222 --> 01:06:10.722
to try to develop, collect these models, and do some

1110
01:06:10.762 --> 01:06:14.482
experiments to give us some clue as to the

1111
01:06:14.522 --> 01:06:18.402
relative homogeneity, heterogeneity of this population, and maybe

1112
01:06:18.442 --> 01:06:22.122
give us an inclination as to possible therapies that could

1113
01:06:22.162 --> 01:06:25.982
be translated into the clinic. So we did this just the way

1114
01:06:26.062 --> 01:06:27.702
we did with sporadic patients.

1115
01:06:28.562 --> 01:06:32.202
We had to get the tumor right away. It had to be processed very precisely,

1116
01:06:32.682 --> 01:06:35.782
and then we had to implant them into the mice and propagate them.

1117
01:06:36.142 --> 01:06:39.932
And I'm now going to report on the models that we have generated and

1118
01:06:40.022 --> 01:06:43.950
characterizedSo the first three models

1119
01:06:44.730 --> 01:06:47.030
were from three different individuals.

1120
01:06:47.870 --> 01:06:50.310
Patient one and patient three

1121
01:06:51.130 --> 01:06:53.930
were very young. Patient one was 13

1122
01:06:54.730 --> 01:06:58.010
and subsequently succumbed to the head-neck cancer before we could

1123
01:06:58.090 --> 01:07:01.630
even really characterize the tumor and do the experiments.

1124
01:07:02.050 --> 01:07:05.710
Patient three also died from a recurrent head-neck

1125
01:07:05.770 --> 01:07:08.930
cancer, an individual in his early 30s.

1126
01:07:09.270 --> 01:07:11.590
Patient two, however, is still alive.

1127
01:07:11.650 --> 01:07:14.790
And because this is such a small community, I've met this patient.

1128
01:07:14.870 --> 01:07:18.350
I've met his family. He's already had two head-neck

1129
01:07:18.390 --> 01:07:22.010
cancers. And so there was somewhat a sense of an urgent need

1130
01:07:22.410 --> 01:07:26.050
to be able to identify a potential target for when

1131
01:07:26.130 --> 01:07:29.090
he develops his recurrence or his third primary

1132
01:07:29.150 --> 01:07:33.070
tumor. So the first thing we asked is, even though platinum

1133
01:07:33.450 --> 01:07:37.270
is contraindicated for patients with Fanconi anemia, is

1134
01:07:37.330 --> 01:07:41.290
it possible that they would be exquisitely sensitive and we

1135
01:07:41.350 --> 01:07:44.750
could find a low dose of platinum that would be

1136
01:07:44.810 --> 01:07:48.510
tolerated and also effective? And I think the answer

1137
01:07:48.590 --> 01:07:52.490
is maybe. I'm not sure. So clearly, there was a dose

1138
01:07:52.530 --> 01:07:56.310
response to platinum among all three

1139
01:07:56.430 --> 01:07:59.980
of our Fanconi anemia PDX models. And we've

1140
01:08:00.050 --> 01:08:03.910
characterized platinum response across a larger number of sporadic

1141
01:08:04.250 --> 01:08:07.800
head neck cancer models, and I think you can appreciate that

1142
01:08:08.670 --> 01:08:12.630
two of the Fanconi models are by far

1143
01:08:12.670 --> 01:08:16.630
the most sensitive to platinum of all the models that we tested.

1144
01:08:16.710 --> 01:08:20.490
One is intermediate, but it is possible that that could be tested.

1145
01:08:20.500 --> 01:08:24.391
It would have to be done really carefully. We have to think of the right platform.

1146
01:08:24.431 --> 01:08:28.070
Would this be an N of one platform? It probably could not be a broad

1147
01:08:28.110 --> 01:08:32.070
clinical trial. And of course, what we're encountering week in

1148
01:08:32.110 --> 01:08:36.050
and week out with the clinicians is we're so wired as clinicians to

1149
01:08:36.110 --> 01:08:40.010
do no harm and to not give a treatment that we know is going to be associated

1150
01:08:40.030 --> 01:08:44.010
with toxicity. But the consequence is we don't give any treatment at

1151
01:08:44.130 --> 01:08:47.830
all, and that is why these patients virtually all

1152
01:08:47.870 --> 01:08:50.969
eventually die of their head and neck cancer.

1153
01:08:51.749 --> 01:08:55.431
So I started studying epidermal growth factor receptor.

1154
01:08:55.811 --> 01:08:59.570
We now know it's an established therapeutic target for

1155
01:08:59.610 --> 01:09:03.250
sporadic head neck cancer. The monoclonal

1156
01:09:03.311 --> 01:09:07.110
antibody cetuximab has been FDA approved for 20

1157
01:09:07.170 --> 01:09:11.130
years. And it's usually given in lieu of platinum in patients

1158
01:09:11.150 --> 01:09:14.780
who can't tolerate platinum, and it's variably used all over the

1159
01:09:14.870 --> 01:09:18.410
world. We never have been able to identify

1160
01:09:18.431 --> 01:09:21.190
predictive biomarkers for cetuximab.

1161
01:09:21.670 --> 01:09:24.710
20% of the patients with sporadic head neck cancer will respond.

1162
01:09:25.090 --> 01:09:28.990
It doesn't appear to have anything to do with the EGFR dose,

1163
01:09:29.070 --> 01:09:32.950
expression level, status. But we asked the question, maybe it's a little

1164
01:09:32.990 --> 01:09:34.910
bit different for Fanconi patients.

1165
01:09:35.271 --> 01:09:38.650
So I think you can appreciate that when we profiled EGFR

1166
01:09:38.690 --> 01:09:42.431
expression in the three tumors, it was

1167
01:09:42.530 --> 01:09:46.090
only really expressed to any substantial degree in

1168
01:09:46.891 --> 01:09:47.790
model number one.

1169
01:09:48.870 --> 01:09:52.811
And we're going to talk a little bit more about the high phosphorylated AKT

1170
01:09:52.851 --> 01:09:56.510
in model number three. I kind of went over this quickly, but

1171
01:09:57.370 --> 01:10:01.210
model number three has a canonical mutation in the PIK3CA

1172
01:10:01.270 --> 01:10:04.850
oncogene. So it's not at all surprising that they have activation of

1173
01:10:04.870 --> 01:10:08.849
phosphorylated AKT. And indeed, when we looked at the

1174
01:10:08.870 --> 01:10:12.789
response to cetuximab across these models, model

1175
01:10:12.850 --> 01:10:16.450
number one, expressing very high levels of EGFR, was exquisitely

1176
01:10:16.570 --> 01:10:20.430
sensitive to cetuximab, whereas model two and model three were

1177
01:10:20.470 --> 01:10:23.710
completely resistant. So when patient number

1178
01:10:23.790 --> 01:10:27.620
two recurs, we're not going to recommend cetuximab for this

1179
01:10:27.650 --> 01:10:29.970
patient. It doesn't make any sense at all.

1180
01:10:29.990 --> 01:10:33.420
And I will also tell you that there are about 12 case reports in the

1181
01:10:33.510 --> 01:10:37.130
literature of Fanconi patients with head neck cancer getting

1182
01:10:37.170 --> 01:10:40.770
cetuximab. None of them were cured with the therapy, but they

1183
01:10:40.890 --> 01:10:44.410
all tolerated the therapy. And it's possible one could think

1184
01:10:44.530 --> 01:10:48.150
about a clinical trial that the conditions might be

1185
01:10:48.190 --> 01:10:52.160
enriched for a cure, because by the time patients get to a clinical trial,

1186
01:10:52.190 --> 01:10:55.760
it's usually a phase one population, and cure is highly

1187
01:10:55.760 --> 01:10:56.390
unlikely.

1188
01:10:57.710 --> 01:11:01.230
And again, we see heterogeneity of cetuximab

1189
01:11:01.270 --> 01:11:03.870
sensitivity compared to the sporadic model.

1190
01:11:03.990 --> 01:11:07.790
So this model of Fanconi is the third most sensitive

1191
01:11:07.890 --> 01:11:11.350
model to cetuximab. In contrast, the other two

1192
01:11:11.390 --> 01:11:15.030
patients with Fanconi, they were completely resistant to cetuximab.

1193
01:11:15.490 --> 01:11:18.310
So even though these are only three models, they're the only ones in the

1194
01:11:18.370 --> 01:11:22.310
literature, and I think heterogeneity was a theme, and I think what it says

1195
01:11:22.350 --> 01:11:23.280
to me is any

1196
01:11:24.330 --> 01:11:28.270
trial that we do in Fanconi patients, we have to find the

1197
01:11:28.310 --> 01:11:32.210
right balance between understanding it's a rare disorder and the

1198
01:11:32.230 --> 01:11:35.730
patients are rare or less common, and they're going to be

1199
01:11:35.770 --> 01:11:39.750
heterogeneous. So developing a precision medicine approach in this condition

1200
01:11:39.810 --> 01:11:42.810
is going to be challenging, but I think a really important guiding light.

1201
01:11:43.730 --> 01:11:47.710
So in addition, biochemically, cetuximab in the model where it was

1202
01:11:47.830 --> 01:11:51.710
active did what it's supposed to do in terms of decreasing PARP

1203
01:11:51.730 --> 01:11:55.610
expression as well as phosphorylated EGFR

1204
01:11:55.650 --> 01:11:58.090
expression and total EGFR downregulation.

1205
01:11:59.050 --> 01:12:02.590
Now again, back to model three. So this has a canonical

1206
01:12:02.600 --> 01:12:06.170
PIK3CA mutation. I believe it's of the helical domain

1207
01:12:06.550 --> 01:12:10.090
E545K, and again, it has phosphorylated

1208
01:12:10.150 --> 01:12:13.210
AKT. Now I will tell you that Alpelisa,

1209
01:12:13.350 --> 01:12:17.050
BYL719, which is FDA approved for a subset of breast

1210
01:12:17.110 --> 01:12:21.040
cancers who have certain activating mutations, it is

1211
01:12:21.130 --> 01:12:23.550
not standard of care for head neck cancer.

1212
01:12:23.560 --> 01:12:26.500
It has only been tested in a very limited way.

1213
01:12:26.530 --> 01:12:29.560
The future of this drug for sporadic head neck cancer is

1214
01:12:29.610 --> 01:12:33.010
uncertain. But you can see that in this particular model,

1215
01:12:33.430 --> 01:12:36.970
there was a response to BYL alone. There was no

1216
01:12:37.010 --> 01:12:39.690
response to cetuximab because remember, it's insensitive.

1217
01:12:40.050 --> 01:12:43.510
But when we combine cetuximab and BYL, which is a tolerable

1218
01:12:43.610 --> 01:12:47.590
combination in a patient with Fanconi anemia, there appeared to be a

1219
01:12:47.690 --> 01:12:47.990
more

1220
01:12:49.090 --> 01:12:50.930
significant anti-tumor response.

1221
01:12:51.030 --> 01:12:52.450
Again, so if

1222
01:12:53.270 --> 01:12:56.230
the next patient has a PIK3CA mutation,

1223
